folder: Ashland Place & Myrtle Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Ashland Place, west side, north from Myrtle Ave. Also shown is Myrtle Ave., north side, west from Ashland Place. In the foreground, is a part of the structure of the Myrtle Ave., Elevated Line of the B.M.T.

October 31, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Ashland Place & Myrtle Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Ashland Place, east side, north from Myrtle Avenue. In the foreground are several very old frame buildings, two with stuccoed fronts. View 2 shows the old buildings, viewed southward toward Myrtle Avenue. This area will later become part of Fort Greene Houses.

View 1: October 12, 1940
View 2: July 1, 1934
View 3: April 21, 1941

P. L. Sperr

View 3 shows Ashland Place (left) running north from Johnson Street (one block north of Myrtle Ave), with all the buildings on the east side of the street cleared for the new housing center. In the background is the Brooklyn Navy Yard.

folder: Myrtle Avenue & Ashland Place, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Myrtle Avenue, north side, east from Ashland Place to St. Edwards Street. All the buildings seen here will be torn down to make way for the erection of Fort Greene Houses, a low-rent housing project.

October 12, 1940

P. L. Sperr
